"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1058789","Department for Education","false","2019-02-19","<p>The Department publishes the amount spent by schools on agency supply teaching staff (as well as costs and receipts from supply teacher insurance) annually for local authority maintained schools, and for academies. Published schools’ Consistent Financial Reporting and Academies’ Accounting Returns are available at the following link: <a href="https://schools-financial-benchmarking.service.gov.uk/Help/DataSources" target="_blank">https://schools-financial-benchmarking.service.gov.uk/Help/DataSources</a>.</p><p>Data from previous years is also available, for local authority maintained schools from 2010, and for academies from 2012.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2019-02-19T17:06:46.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1058789/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1058789/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1058789/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-02-11","Supply Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate he has made of the amount spent by schools in England on agency supply teachers for each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sarah Jones","Croydon Central","Sarah Jones","219550"
