"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1058837","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-02-14","<p>In the last two years, the value of the contracts held by the Ministry of Defence (MOD) with Deloitte was £58.948 million, and those with Mott MacDonald totalled £120.275 million.</p><p>The MOD has held no contracts with Slaughter and May within the last two years.</p><p>Information about the contracts that we place with industry is available on GOV.uk as part of our MOD Trade, Industry and Contracts statistics:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/defence-trade-and-industry-index</p><p>In addition, MOD contracts worth over £10,000 are published on the Government's Contracts Finder website, which is available on GOV.uk at: https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2019-02-14T15:56:11.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1058837/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1058837/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1058837/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-02-11","Ministry of Defence: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the value of contracts held by his Department with (a) Deloitte, (b) Slaughter and May and (c) Mott MacDonald is in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","219285"
